				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				3 tries so far, 3 failures at fletching 102, gonna try more this weekend (maybe if i'm smart i'll get my fletching up some more first)<BR>
<BR>
quick math:<BR>
<BR>
for every time you turn in the bag you need one of each:wood, wire, silk, servo.<BR>
<BR>
then you need to combine the bowstaff, wire, and servo.<BR>
<BR>
for every wire you need 2 tumpy's<BR>
for every tumpy you need a nut and a water.<BR>
<BR>
so if you're gonna try 10 times you need to get 20 each of wires and servo's<BR>
<BR>
which means you need 40 tumpy's<BR>
which means you're gonna need 40 nuts and 40 waters..<BR>
<BR>
my point - plan ahead, after 3 tries, i still had 5 wires and 9 pieces of wood left over because i didn't get enough nuts or enough servos.<BR>
<BR>
dave
